      "content": "Melatonin and zolpidem work in different ways, and combining them is a risky shortcut to sleep. Since you need to be functional tomorrow, I recommend you take a full 10-20 minutes before bed, take your melatonin, and then take the zolpidem exactly as prescribed, perhaps a little later if you need it. For a guaranteed, safe sleep, you need to follow the instructions for each medication individually, and you should definitely get a full check-in with your doctor about your sleep strategy.",
      "source": "target",
